David Cameron last night urged wobbling European leaders not to go soft on Vladimir Putin in the wake of a ‘ceasefire’ in Ukraine.

At an EU summit in Brussels, the Prime Minister insisted Europe must stand firm in maintaining sanctions against Russia.

His comments came after the leaders of Russia, Ukraine, France and Germany reached a deal to end the spiralling bloodshed in the region after a tense 17 hours of negotiations.

