Several countries – including Greece, whose new far-Left government has been cosying up to Moscow – are understood to be seeking to unpick the embargoes put in place when Putin invaded Crimea. 

Meanwhile, fighting continued in eastern Ukraine last night as 50 tanks and 40 armoured vehicles crossed the border, Ukrainians claimed.

